HEADWORD: Terneplate
<hw>Terne"plate`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Tern</er>, <pos>a.</pos>, and <er>Plate</er>.]</ety> <def>Thin iron
sheets coated with an alloy of lead and tin; -- so called because made
up of <xex>three</xex> metals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

